Key Match Events: Tatum hit a 3-pointer at the buzzer in overtime as the Celtics rallied to beat the Toronto Raptors 126-123 on Saturday night.
Barrett connected on a runner in the lane and was fouled by Brown with 59 seconds remaining, but missed his ensuing free throw.
Boston’s Neemias Queta scored a driving layup on Boston’s next possession.

Toronto won a coach’s challenge on an out of bounds call that originally was awarded to Boston, but Barrett had his driving layup attempt blocked by Queta, giving the ball back to the Celtics with 20.2 seconds remaining.
Post-Match Reflections: Tatum finished with 24 points and 11 rebounds as the Celtics improved to 11-3.
Jaylen Brown added 27 points. Al Horford and Derrick White scored 18 points apiece.
Toronto has lost seven straight and failed to register its first road win of the season, despite getting a career-high 35 points from Jakob Poeltl.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Toronto outscored the Celtics 76-42 in the paint.
The Raptors outscored the Celtics 76-42 in the paint.
Boston gave up 68 points to Atlanta during its NBA Cup loss to the Hawks earlier this week.
